                                              MARKER INTERFACE
                                              =================


NOTE: If interface does not have any method then it is called as "MARKER INTERFACE.."

     Ex: Clonable, Serializable......

==> If our class implements predefined marker interface then JVM will treat our classes as special classes and JVM will provide special functionality.
Example: 

public interface Demo{

  }

public class test implements Demo{

  }

Note: We can create our own marker interfaces but there is no use because JVM don't know about our marker interfaces.


